        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2009-04-15T19:07:09Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Helping Americans Keep Their Homes Act of 2009 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to: (1) increase from $10,000 to $15,000 the limit on penalty-free distributions from tax-exempt retirement plans for the purchase of a principal residence by a first-time homebuyer; (2) suspend the first-time homebuyer requirement for such distributions that are made before January 1, 2011; and (3) exempt loans from individual retirement accounts (IRAs) used to refinance a principal residence from certain prohibited transaction tax rules until 2011. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
